<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1587> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1587" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "C. Livius succeeded M. Pomponius Matho." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1586> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1586" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Bardt (11) has seen that it is not possible to identify this M. Pomponius Matho with certainty. See 217, note 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1584> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1584" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 26.23.7-8" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1225> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1225" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Act. Tr. (names entire); Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Zon. 8.18; and on Fabius, Cic. Sen. 10; Elogia, CIL 1\n     .1, p. 193- Inscr. Ital. 13.3.14 and 80; Degrassi 44f., 117, 438f. Fabius celebrated a triumph over the Ligurians (Act. Tr., Degrassi 76f., 549; Elog., as above; Cic. Pis. 58; Plut. Fab. 2.1; Comp. Per. and Fab. 2.1; Auct. Vir. Ill. 43; Zon. 8.18); and dedicated a temple of Honos (Cic. ND 2.61). On his threat to Carthage, see Gell. 10.27.3-5; Zon. 8.18. Pomponius campaigned in Sardinia and celebrated a triumph (Act. Tr., Degrassi 78f., 549; cf. Zon. 8.18). On Pomponius, see D.- G. 5.3ff., no. 5." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10186> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10186" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Sardeis. MRR I.224, Itgenshorst no. 149, Rich no. 148." .
